Microbiome analysis - data prep

Maureen A. Carey

Metadata variables: Metadata variables included age-related information (month/year of birth, age in days), socio-economic status (income, perceived food deficit), time of collection (month, year, amount of rainfall that month), the childs home conditions (presence of an indoor drain, drinking water source, water treatment method, number of children under the age of 5 years), coinfection status (positive qPCR for Giardia spp. or E. histolytica), repeat infection v. primary infection, and growth status (z-scores for weight-for-age, height-for-age, weight-for-height, and body mass index for age). These are known to influence the development of diarrhea broadly or the acquisition of Cryptosporidium (Korpe et al.2016; Steiner et al.2018; Mondal et al.2012)

Code for reference: /Users/maureencarey/local_documents/work/crypto_microbiome/data_cannot_be_shared/open_and_save_all_data.Rmd to generate /Users/maureencarey/local_documents/work/crypto_microbiome/data_cannot_be_shared/data.RData

The above code processes the private patient metadata and so cannot be shared at this point.
